The paper discusses the detection of adversarial examples in the domain of machine learning-based image classification, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also mentions the broader security context, indicating a potential overlap with computer security (cs.CR). The use of neural networks and machine learning suggests a potential overlap with machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper highlights the parallels between adversarial classification and multimedia forensics, indicating a potential overlap with multimedia (cs.MM).
